Check column names across years for a dataset

Source: R/dev_tools.R
nhstt_check_columns.Rd

Displays a detailed comparison of column names across all years for a specific table, showing which columns are present in all years vs missing in some years. Uses colour-coded output for easy visual inspection.

Usage

nhstt_check_columns(raw_data, table_name, clean_names = TRUE)

Arguments

raw_data

Raw data from nhstt_get_raw()

table_name

Name of table to check (e.g., "main", "therapy_type", "therapist_role")

clean_names

Logical, whether to apply janitor::make_clean_names() before comparison. Default is TRUE to match how tidy pipeline processes names.

Value

Invisibly returns list with complete columns, partial columns, and presence matrix

Examples

# \donttest{
raw <- nhstt_get_raw()
#> ℹ Downloading raw data for 8 periods
#> Downloading ■■■■■■■■■■■■                     3/8
#> Downloading ■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■                 4/8
#> Downloading ■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■          6/8
#> Downloading ■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■  8/8
#> 
#> ✔ Downloaded 8 periods

# Check main dataset
nhstt_check_columns(raw, "key_measures")
